# PaleoClaw .env example
#
# Quick start:
# 1) Copy this file to `.env` (for local runs from this repo), OR to `~/.paleoclaw/.env` (for launchd/systemd daemons).
# 2) Fill only the values you use.
# 3) Keep real secrets out of git.
#
# Env-source precedence for environment variables (highest -> lowest):
# process env, ./.env, ~/.paleoclaw/.env, then paleoclaw.json `env` block.
# Note: direct config keys (for example `gateway.auth.token` or channel tokens in paleoclaw.json)
# are resolved separately from env loading and might take precedence over env fallbacks.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Gateway auth + paths
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Recommended if the gateway binds beyond loopback.
PALEOCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=change-me-to-a-long-random-token
# Example generator: openssl rand -hex 32

# Optional alternative auth mode (use token OR password).
# PALEOCLAW_GATEWAY_PASSWORD=change-me-to-a-strong-password

# Optional path overrides (defaults shown for reference).
# PALEOCLAW_STATE_DIR=~/.paleoclaw
# PALEOCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=~/.paleoclaw/paleoclaw.json
# PALEOCLAW_HOME=~

# Optional: import missing keys from your login shell profile.
# PALEOCLAW_LOAD_SHELL_ENV=1
# PALEOCLAW_SHELL_ENV_TIMEOUT_MS=15000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AI Model provider API keys (set at least one)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# For paleontology research, recommended models:
# - OpenAI: gpt-5-mini, gpt-5.4 (best for scientific reasoning)
# - Qwen: qwen-plus-latest (good for Chinese literature)
# - Gemini: gemini-flash-latest (fast, good for summaries)

# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# PALEOCLAW_AI_PROVIDER=openai
# PALEOCLAW_AI_MODEL=gpt-5-mini

# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...
# QWEN_API_KEY=...
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# Live test keys (for testing)
# PALEOCLAW_LIVE_OPENAI_KEY=sk-...
# PALEOCLAW_LIVE_ANTHROPIC_KEY=sk-ant-...
# PALEOCLAW_LIVE_GEMINI_KEY=...

# Multiple API keys for failover
# OPENAI_API_KEYS=sk-1,sk-2
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEYS=sk-ant-1,sk-ant-2
# GEMINI_API_KEYS=key-1,key-2

# Optional additional providers
# ZAI_API_KEY=...
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=...
# MINIMAX_API_KEY=...
# SYNTHETIC_API_KEY=...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Channels (only set what you enable)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# For research team collaboration:

# Telegram (recommended for research teams)
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABCDEF...

# Discord (good for lab groups)
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=...

# Slack (academic institutions)
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
# SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...

# Optional channel env fallbacks
# MATTERMOST_BOT_TOKEN=...
# MATTERMOST_URL=https://chat.example.com
# ZALO_BOT_TOKEN=...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Research Tools (optional)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Literature search enhancements
# BRAVE_API_KEY=...  # For web search
# PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=pplx-...  # AI search
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=...  # Web scraping for open-access papers

# Voice/media (for presentations)
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=...
# XI_API_KEY=...  # alias for ElevenLabs
# DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=...  # Speech-to-text

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PaleoClaw Research Settings
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default research workspace
# PALEOCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR=~/paleoclaw-workspace

# PBDB API settings (no key required, but can set custom endpoint)
# PALEOCLAW_PBDB_BASE_URL=https://paleobiodb.org/data1.2/

# CrossRef settings (polite pool)
# PALEOCLAW_CROSSREF_MAILTO=your.email@institution.edu

# Cache directory for API responses
# PALEOCLAW_CACHE_DIR=~/.paleoclaw/cache

# Rate limiting (requests per minute)
# PALEOCLAW_PBDB_RATE_LIMIT=100
# PALEOCLAW_CROSSREF_RATE_LIMIT=50
